						<summary>

						<p>On a hero-stone in front of a ruined temple on the way to the ferry.</p>						

						<p>Dated Śaka 978 (= A.D. 1056-57).</p>						

						<p>Records the death of Mallaya Kāmaṇḍu in a fight on behalf of his master. States that the memorial stone was the work of Āvegaḍa Sarasvati. Refers to one Vākōju along with Sarasvati.</p>						

						</summary>
